 203:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
 204:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      Use function HAL_OSPI_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback,
 205:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      it allows to register following callbacks:
 206:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) ErrorCallback : callback when error occurs.
 207:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) AbortCpltCallback : callback when abort is completed.
 208:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) FifoThresholdCallback : callback when the fifo threshold is reached.
 209:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) CmdCpltCallback : callback when a command without data is completed.
 210:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) RxCpltCallback : callback when a reception transfer is completed.
 211:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) TxCpltCallback : callback when a transmission transfer is completed.
 212:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) RxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the reception transfer is completed.
 213:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) TxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the transmission transfer is completed.
 214:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) StatusMatchCallback : callback when a status match occurs.
 215:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) TimeOutCallback : callback when the timeout perioed expires.
 216:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) MspInitCallback    : OSPI MspInit.
 217:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) MspDeInitCallback  : OSPI MspDeInit.
 218:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
 219:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 220:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      and a pointer to the user callback function.
 221:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c **** 
 222:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
 223:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      Use function HAL_OSPI_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 224:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      weak (overridden) function. It allows to reset following callbacks:
 225:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) ErrorCallback : callback when error occurs.
 226:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) AbortCpltCallback : callback when abort is completed.
 227:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) FifoThresholdCallback : callback when the fifo threshold is reached.
 228:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) CmdCpltCallback : callback when a command without data is completed.
 229:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) RxCpltCallback : callback when a reception transfer is completed.
 230:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) TxCpltCallback : callback when a transmission transfer is completed.
 231:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) RxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the reception transfer is completed.
 232:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) TxHalfCpltCallback : callback when half of the transmission transfer is completed.
 233:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) StatusMatchCallback : callback when a status match occurs.
 234:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) TimeOutCallback : callback when the timeout perioed expires.
 235:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) MspInitCallback    : OSPI MspInit.
 236:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      (+) MspDeInitCallback  : OSPI MspDeInit.
 237:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
 238:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      This function) takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle and the Callback ID.
 239:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c **** 
 240:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
 241:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      By default, after the HAL_OSPI_Init() and if the state is HAL_OSPI_STATE_RESET
 242:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak (overridden) functions.
 243:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
 244:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      reset to the legacy weak (overridden) functions in the HAL_OSPI_Init()
 245:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      and HAL_OSPI_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 246:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_OSPI_Init() and HAL_OSPI_DeInit()
 247:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 248:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c **** 
 249:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****     [..]
 250:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
 251:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
 252:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 253:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      during the Init/DeInit.
 254:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 255:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      using HAL_OSPI_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_OSPI_DeInit()
 256:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c ****      or HAL_OSPI_Init() function.
 257:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_ospi.c **** 
